If going into that other direction, I think the function would be:
```c
/// Check that mouse support is enabled for visual mode
static bool mouse_supports_visual(void)
{
  return p_mouse[0] == '\0' || vim_strchr(p_mouse, 'a') != NULL
    || vim_strchr(p_mouse, 'v') != NULL;
}
```

EDIT: It misses the case for help files, I'm not completely sure about it. Also it's easier to read with strchr, and as `mouse` is very short there is no overhead doing multiple loops over it.

